49    /**
50    * Compiler pass that computes function purity. A function is pure if
51    * it has no outside visible side effects, and the result of the
52    * computation does not depend on external factors that are beyond the
53    * control of the application; repeated calls to the function should
54    * return the same value as long as global state hasn't changed.
55    *
56    * Date.now is an example of a function that has no side effects but
57    * is not pure.
58    *
59    *
60    * We will prevail, in peace and freedom from fear, and in true
61    * health, through the purity and essence of our natural... fluids.
62    * - General Turgidson
63    */
